Magrittr makes the code more readable

head(melt(as.data.frame(lapply(sapply(city, unique), length))))
##           variable value
## 1     name_of_city   492
## 2       state_code    29
## 3       state_name    29
## 4        dist_code    61
## 5 population_total   493
## 6  population_male   493
unique = sapply(city, unique) %>% lapply(., length) %>% as.data.frame(.) %>% melt()

unique %>% head(.)
##           variable value
## 1     name_of_city   492
## 2       state_code    29
## 3       state_name    29
## 4        dist_code    61
## 5 population_total   493
## 6  population_male   493
unique %>% ggplot(.,aes(x = variable, y = value)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity')

unique %>% ggplot(.,aes(x = reorder(variable,value), y = value)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity') 

unique %>% ggplot(.,aes(x = reorder(variable,value), y = value)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity') + 
  coord_flip()

unique %>% ggplot(.,aes(x = reorder(variable,value), y = value)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity') + 
  coord_flip() + 
  geom_text(aes(label = value),hjust = -.05) 

unique %>% ggplot(.,aes(x = reorder(variable,value), y = value)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity') + 
  coord_flip() + 
  geom_text(aes(label = value),hjust = -.05) + 
  labs(x = "Variables", y = "Unique count", title = "Indian city")

#State vs Number of city in top 500
state_city_count = aggregate(formula = name_of_city~state_name, data = city, FUN = length)

ggplot(state_city_count, aes(x = reorder(state_name,name_of_city), y = name_of_city)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity' , fill = "lightblue" , colour = "black") + 
  coord_flip() +
  geom_text(aes(label = name_of_city),hjust = -.3) +
  labs(x = "State", y = "# City", title = "Indian city")

#Literacy rate distribution
ggplot(city,aes(x = effective_literacy_rate_total)) + 
  geom_histogram(colour = "white" , fill = "#008080")

#State average litracy rate
state_mean_literacy = aggregate(formula = effective_literacy_rate_total~state_name,
                                data = city,
                                FUN = mean)

state_mean_literacy %>% head(.)
##                  state_name effective_literacy_rate_total
## 1 ANDAMAN & NICOBAR ISLANDS                      89.76000
## 2            ANDHRA PRADESH                      80.92786
## 3                     ASSAM                      91.51250
## 4                     BIHAR                      80.86769
## 5                CHANDIGARH                      86.77000
## 6              CHHATTISGARH                      87.13889
state_mean_literacy %>% 
  ggplot(.,aes(x = reorder(state_name,effective_literacy_rate_total) ,
               y = effective_literacy_rate_total)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity') + 
  coord_flip() + 
  labs(x = "State", y = "Literacy rate",title = "State literacy rate")

#City with High literacy rate
attach(city)
city[effective_literacy_rate_total > 95,] %>% 
  ggplot(.,aes( x = reorder(name_of_city,effective_literacy_rate_total),
                y = effective_literacy_rate_total)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity') + 
  coord_flip() + 
  geom_text(aes(label = state_name)) +
  labs(x = "City",y = "Literacy rate", title = "City with High literacy rate")

detach(city)
#City with Least literacy rate
attach(city)
city[effective_literacy_rate_total < 70,] %>% 
  ggplot(.,aes( x = reorder(name_of_city,effective_literacy_rate_total),
                y = effective_literacy_rate_total)) + 
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity') + 
  coord_flip() + 
  geom_text(aes(label = state_name)) +
  labs(x = "City",y = "Literacy rate", title = "City with Least literacy rate")

detach(city)
  
#State vs gender
state_literacy_gender = city[,c("state_name","effective_literacy_rate_male","effective_literacy_rate_female")]
state_literacy_gender = melt(c("state_name"),data = state_literacy_gender) 
#boxplot
ggplot(state_literacy_gender, aes( x = variable,y = value , fill = variable)) + 
  geom_boxplot() + 
  labs(x = "Gender", y = "Literacy rate" )

#histogram
ggplot(state_literacy_gender,aes(x = value,fill = variable)) + 
  geom_histogram() + 
  facet_grid(variable~.) +
  labs(x = "Literacy  rate", y = "Frequency", title = "Male vs Female")

#density plot
ggplot(state_literacy_gender,aes(x = value,fill = variable)) + geom_density(alpha = .6)

#heat map
ggplot(state_literacy_gender,aes(x = variable, y = state_name, fill = value)) + 
  geom_tile()+
  labs(x = "Literacy rate", y = "State")

# Scatter plot
ggplot(city,aes(x = effective_literacy_rate_male , 
                y = child_sex_ratio)) + 
  geom_point(colour = "#841F27",size = 4, alpha = .4) +
  labs(x = "Male litracy rate",y = "child sex ratio")

ggplot(city,aes(x = effective_literacy_rate_female , 
                y = child_sex_ratio)) + 
  geom_point(colour = "#841F27",size = 4, alpha = .4) +
  labs(x = "female litracy rate",y = "child sex ratio")
